About
Bringing people together, connecting and inspiring them by organising and facilitating meaningful encounters. We do this from our multifunctional exhibition and conference centre on Europaplein in Amsterdam, as well as elsewhere in the world where we operate.

Handy Exhibition Center at South Amsterdam City Area
Mar 2023
Very modern style exhibition center, with several separate halls, so there are usual many different kind of exhibitions going on, at the same day. I visited at special theme, during 3 days, finding that easiest way was to choose metro line towards Europaplein, and walk from there. When you choose right exit you'll be at the front of entrances. As it was (not yet) any hot summer (peak) seasons, they used plenty of warming/heating equipments inside. It was still comfortable climate inside.

This is not a theatre and shouldn't pretend to be
Feb 2020
We paid 143 euro to attend a performance of Shen Yun in the (so-called) RAI theatre.Our seats were four rows back and in the middle. We confidently expected a great view of this dance spectacle. What a disappointment! The seating is such that our view was blocked by those in front of us.
I complained to the RAI. They explained the 'theatre' was designed for congresses - and so a static speaker in the middle of the stage. They claimed that the organisers (Shen Yun) were aware of this limitation.

Huge but with good facilities
Sep 2019
Massive exhibition hall which is so big I still continue to get lost around despite visiting numerous times. Fortunately all the staff who work there are friendly and there is always plenty employed to be on hand when you need them. Good facilities and plenty of clean toilets mean spending long days at work there could be a lot more painful than it is. Theres always lots of options for food, including proper sit down restaurants inside, but they are all expensive for what they are. Overall a very impressive place though!

ColConnie
Des Plaines, Illinois
130 contributions
The meeting I attended at the RAI utilized the RAI facilities. There are numerous meeting room in addition to larger auditorium and exhibit spaces. There was coffee service in addition to lunch and breakfast. Coming back and forth from the hotel, we did note dozens of restaurants within a block of the RAI, but we did not visit any of them. We elected to take our evening meals on a dinner cruise or downtown near the canals. If your main meeting is at the RAI you may want to investigate the cost of a small meeting room. There is a coffee shop that ight be usable as well. Otherwise when you arrive, you may want to take a quick walk around the neighborhood and select the appropraite eatery for your purposes.
Written August 23, 2015
